    "bio2": "Since retiring from railroad service, he has been an independent consultant specializing in reducing greenhouse gas emissions within the rail transportation and trucking sector as well as safety and operational analytics.    Wayne holds a BS in Mechanical Engineering from Brigham Young University and an MBA from the University of Nebraska Omaha. He is a member of multiple rail industry committees including LMOA and ASLRRA where he has published and presented various papers on railroad fuel efficiency.  He holds five patents, mostly in the rail aerodynamics space.",
